@Node INTR "Introduction to this PowerDOOR"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                        Introduction - What is it?
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   Power Poll is a Voting System that allows Users of any MAXs Bulletin
   Board System to vote on any topic specified by the SysOp of the BBS.

   This allows SysOps to vote on whether to change certain aspects of
   their BBS which means that Users will not be upset if you change the
   Filebase or whatever.

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                        What does this Door offer?
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   This Door offers Two unique doors. One is the main Voting Door which
   includes a Sysop Menu and a Previous Results viewing System. The
   other door is intended to add to LogOff Scripts or in LogOn scripts.
   The second Door is a results Door which displays the current poll
   results and then exits after a key is pressed.

   This Door also offers Logging capabilities. It logs whenever a New
   Poll Question is devised storing the Questions in the Log-File as
   well. Whenever someone votes, Their details are recorded with the
   Reply they voted for. The log-file can be found in `BBS:LogFiles'
   and is called `PowerPOLL_Log.Text'.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode INTR

@Node INST "Installing PowerDOORS"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                     Installation of this PowerDOOR...
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   All PowerDOORS are installed in the same way. Simply, make sure that
   there is a directory in your Doors directory or assignment called
   `POWER'. This is where all PowerDOORS are stored. If you do not have
   your DOORS directory assigned, then you should add an Assign to your
   Startup-Sequence or User-Startup File.

        C:Assign >NIL: DOORS: BBS:Doors/
                              ^^^^^^^^^^
                              Change this to your Doors directory path

   Now, Create a directory inside the `DOORS:Power/' Directory with
   the name of the Door. This is the word to the right of the `Power'
   in the Archive filename. So, For example, if the PowerDOOR was called
   PowerPOLL, then you would create a directory in the `DOORS:Power/'
   directory called `POLL'.

   Now, Locate the Archive you downloaded or received. It will probably
   be in the `LhA' or `LZX' form. Simply use a version of `LhA' or `LZX'
   to Extract the files into the desired path.

    C:LhA x PowerPOLL_??.LHA DOORS:Power/POLL/  \  Where `????' is the
                                                 } Name of the PowerDOOR
    C:LZX x PowerPOLL_??.LZX DOORS:Power/POLL/  /  For example, `POLL'

   Now, all the files including some File Descriptions `File_ID.DIZ' and
   some Configuration files `Poll.CFG'. Other files will also be
   included which are not Doors such as those that have the File
   Extension of `.Text'. These files are ANSIs. If you find a file with
   an extension of `.DAT', then do not try and edit these.

   Now, You must add the Door to a MAXsBBS Menu or to one of the
   Log-on Scripts.

    MAXsBBS Menu
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Simply go to the relevant Menu where you want to add the Polling Door
   or Results Door and enter the following details in the Menu Editor.

   Key  Func  Extra  Lo Acc  Hi Acc  Path/Filename/Extra...
   ~~~  ~~~~  ~~~~~  ~~~~~~  ~~~~~~  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   ???    34      0   ?????   ?????  POWER:Poll/Poll
   ???    34      0   ?????   ?????  POWER:Poll/Results

    Logon Scripts
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Load in either `DOORS:IntroDoor.Text' or `DOORS:MainDoor.Text' into
   any AmigaDOS Text Editor such as `Ed' or `Memacs' and add the
   following wherever you would like to Doors to run...

      Power/Poll/Poll         <- Poll Door
      Power/Poll/Results      <- Results Door

   As from version 1.2, You will now be able to record who votes for
   what thanks to a unique log recording feature. Simply check the File
   called `PowerPOLL_Log.Text' located in the `BBS:LogFiles/' Directory.

   @{" [C] " Link CONF} Configuration

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode INST

@Node CONF "Configuring PowerDOORS"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                       Configuration of PowerDOORS
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   All PowerDOORS are configured in the same way. In the PowerDOOR
   archive (or Directory if extracted), You will find file(s) with an
   extension of `.CFG', These are @{b}C@{ub}on@{b}F@{ub}i@{b}G@{ub}uration files.

   Simply load these Configuration (CFG) Files into a Text Editor and
   either follow the simple guide located at the end of the Configuration
   files or use the more complex guide which is located in the Door Guide.

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
    Layout for the Configuration                               PowerPOLL
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

  << @{b}Line 01@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename of an ANSI/Text File
   that is displayed during the main operation of the Voting Door.
   Please check the Example ANSI (`Poll.Text') for more details on
   Layout and Positions.

  << @{b}Line 02@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename of an ANSI/Text File
   that represents the SysOp's Control Menu for PowerPOLL. This menu
   must contain the Key shortcuts that reset the Poll counts and start
   new counts. Check the (`SysOp.Text') ANSI File for more information.

  << @{b}Line 03@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename of an ANSI/Text File
   that displays the Previous Poll Results. See 'Results.Text' for more
   Details.

  << @{b}Line 04@{ub} >> - @{i} Path & Filename @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Path and Filename of an ANSI/Text File
   that is displayed when displaying the Results of the Current Poll
   from the seperate `Results' door that is included. Check the ANSI
   File called `Final_Results.Text' for more details.

  << @{b}Line 05@{ub} >> - @{i} Number - Y Coordinate @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain a Number that represents the Y coordinate
   at which the Question set by the SysOp on line 7 of this Configuration
   is displayed (Centred) on. The default is about `8' or `9'.

  << @{b}Line 06@{ub} >> - @{i} Title @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain a Title that will appear at the top of
   the Screen. This Title should represent the Title of the current
   Polling Topic such as `The Great Spice Girls Poll'.

  << @{b}Line 07@{ub} >> - @{i} The Polling Question @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the actual Polling Question that is
   displayed on the screen for the Users to vote for.

   For example, `Who is the Best Spice Girl?'

  << @{b}Line 08@{ub} >> - @{i} Option A @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the first Reply that is available to the
   Users when they Vote on the Question set on Line 7 of this
   configuration file.

   For example, `Geri'

  << @{b}Line 08@{ub} >> - @{i} Option B @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This line should contain the Second Reply that is available to the
   Users when they Vote on the Question set on Line 7 of this
   configuration file.

   For example, `Emma'

  << @{b}Line 10@{ub} >> - @{i} End of Configuration @{ui}
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   As with all PowerDOORS, The Hash (#) at the end of the Configuration
   signifies its end. Any text after this Hash (either to the right or
   below it) will be ignored by the Door making it useful to add comments
   about the configuration below.
   
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   Now, Save the Configuration File as a Plain ASCII File and not a
   Wordworth or other WP Document. Make sure that the File is saved in
   Plain ASCII otherwise it will not work.

   @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode CONF

@Node USIN "Using the PowerDOOR"

  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
                           Using the PowerDOOR...
  -=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

   Polling/Voting Door
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Main Operation
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   When the Door loads, You can do one of many things. You can exit
   back to the BBS by pressing [ESC]. You could also Vote on the topic
   by Pressing either [A] or [B].

   You can access the Previous Poll Sections by pressing [L] or you
   can access the SysOp Menu by Pressing [S]

    [ESC] - Exit to BBS
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Pressing [ESC] (Escape) will quit PowerPOLL and return you back to
   the BBS. This can be done at anytime except when Disk Access is
   occuring.

    [A] - Voting
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Pressing [A] will add a Vote to the Poll count of `Reply A'. This
   will cause the Poll Count Boxes to update as well as the Percentage
   and Results Graph. After a short burst of Disk access, the Door will
   exit back to the BBS.

    [B] - Voting
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   As with [A], Pressing [B] will increase the Poll count of `Reply B'.
   The Results Tables and Graphs will update and you will be returned
   back to the BBS.

    [L] - Previous Results
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Pressing [L] will take you to the Last Results part of the Door.
   This part will consist of the results and graphs of the Last
   PowerPOLL Vote that occured. You can press [R] to return to the
   main Voting section or press [Q] to exit back to the BBS.

    [S] - SysOp's Menu
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   In the SysOp's Menu, You can reset the Poll Count for Reply `A' back
   to Zero by pressing [1]. You can reset the Poll Count of `B' by
   pressing [2]. To Reset both Poll Counts back to Zero, You can simply
   press [3]. Alternatively, You can start an entirely new poll by
   pressing [4] and then using Keys [1], [2], [A] and [B], You can set
   new Titles, Question and Replies. When done, You can save changes by
   pressing [S] or Quit back to the Poll without saving by pressing [Q].

   [R] will return you to the Main Voting Section and [Q] will exit back
   to the BBS.

   Results Door
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   This Door will load and display the Current Poll results in Table
   and Graphical form. Simply press any key to exit back to the BBS.

  @{" [0] " Link MAIN} Return to the Main Menu

@EndNode USIN

